@Node Lyap

                              Lyapunovia1.5
                             by @{" Sylvia Lutnes " link Syl}

From the documentation for Lyapunovia1.5: "If the Mandelbrot set is the
'most complex object in mathematics', Lyapunov Space must be the
juiciest, spiciest and most outrageous object ever found within numbers."
I agree. Lyapunov pictures are an artist's dream...or nightmare,
depending on your tastes. In one evening of playing with this program I
came up with a dozen pictures I want to use in Imagine.

Lyapunovia1.5 is a shareware program by Jesper Juul of Denmark. This
commercial quality program supports all Amigas and processors (1.3
through 3.0) and even has a version for non-accelerated Amigas that have
a co-processor. Strict adherence to Commodore's style guidelines is
maintained and if you're running 2.1 or better you can even use the
screenmode requester to choose resolution and color depth.  You can set
the priority of the program from its menu...a feature I wish more
programs had. The documentation is thorough and comes in both ascii and
.guide formats.

Pictures can be generated in most Amiga modes, including 256 color AGA,
and saving as 24-bit is supported. This program is extremely easy to use
because the Lyapunov 'formulas' are not difficult to play with. There are
dozens of formulas included, and with the ability to zoom with the mouse
you may never have to enter a formula at all.

The many included 16, 32, and 256 color palettes are amazingly beautiful
and can change your finished picture in a heartbeat into something that
looks totally different. Color cycling is supported, but be careful!  You
may find yourself spending as much time staring at walls of moving lava,
intricate space needles and shimmering @{" web things " system "WDisplay VPort:lyapc"} as generating new
pictures.


Lyapunovia1.5
Jesper Juul
Fred Fish Disk #877
Starship Library File #20075 (417k)
$10 (shareware)

