                  Amiga Artists Continue To Impress Me!
                           by @{" deb Christensen " link deb}

Some people will scoff at you when you suggest that a computer is another
art medium, like oils, watercolors, pastels, or any other number of
traditional artist's tools.  And if all they have ever seen are scanned
pictures of photographs, they might be right in thinking that.

However, this is Amiga Territory now, and I think we have every right to
be proud of the incredible pictures being created on Amigas.  While there
is always someone who wants to look at the latest scanned picture of a
half naked woman, the real art going on is being done by Amiga artists,
each with their own style, each one bringing their own interpretation to
the screens that we see.

I don't know how many times I have said it, but ANYONE can scan a
picture. It takes talent to draw one.  It seems to me that the talented
ones seem to own Amigas.  Amazing coincidence, hmmmm?

With that in mind, I'd like to highlight some of the EXTRAORDINARY and
AMAZING pictures which are featured in Library 19 of the *StarShip* from
recent files.  And I'd like to encourage everyone to look at these,
because this _is_ what Amiga talent is all about.  You will be impressed.
Your friends will, too!

Towards the middle of May, P.MORAWIEC uploaded an extremely large
collection of pictures from the European "GATHERING" in Norway.  Like
many of you, I looked at the filesize, groaned, and put it off for a week.

Oh, was I sorry I tarried in looking at them.  These were INCREDIBLE.

There are *6* pictures in that one file, which I've gone and uploaded
separately, I thought they were so good.  Let me tell you about them...

Number: 20086  Name: THE_DRYADS.LZH             File Size:   75136
   TheDryads.iff is a fantasy scene of three tree spirits, Dryads,
   beautifully created and tastefully wrapped around the trunk of the
   tree.  Remember now, Dryads don't care much about clothing, so these
   three ladies are kind of nude.  If that offends you, skip this file
   and get the OTHER selections from the GATHERING pictures.

Number: 20084  Name: SILKWORM.LZH               File Size:   89856
   She stands victoriously over a great slain worm.  This is like no silk
   worm you have ever seen, more like one from some DM's nightmare!  It is
   our good fortune that this brave warrior-woman was up to the task, and
   wasn't killed by the large beast.

Number: 20082  Name: PENCIL_DRAGON.LZH          File Size:   26240
   This dragon has been inked by the artist, and the pen lays there on
   the pad.  A portion of the dragon has already been painted, in fact.
   Unfortunately for our artist, he started painting the HEAD of the
   dragon FIRST, and well, it came alive!  You will notice there is no
   sign of the artist ANYWHERE in this picture!

Number: 20080  Name: FREAK.LZH                  File Size:   64128
   The Beast pounces from the cliffs, and you'd better be glad he is not
   pouncing at you!  This is another excellent piece of Amiga artwork from
   the huge GATHERING93.LHA file, separated for easier downloading.

Number: 20079  Name: EDDIE_SILVER.LZH           File Size:  101120
   This is a surreal piece of fine Amiga art, Eddie Silver is obviously
   trying to put the pieces together.  It's an excellent picture, and
   an interesting surreal/modern composition.  I think I can almost hear
   some really good MOD playing behind it....

Number: 20078  Name: BATTLEMECH.LZH              File Size:  47744
   Yes, it is a Mech Warrior, aiming his three cannons down the side
   of some bluffs.  I'm glad I'm not looking UP at him!  The Mech itself
   is sleek and sexy looking, there isn't a sharp edge on it anywhere.

You can grab them all at once if you like, from the file:

# 19373 GATHER93.LHA             P.MORAWIEC      File Size: 404864
        Desc: Six great IFFs from Gathering'93


All I can say is ... more!  We want MORE Amiga pictures.  Share your best
with the entire Amiga Community, they just can't do this on a PeeCee. :)

